Gluster 3.2: Manually Mounting Volumes Using NFS[ Manually Mounting
Volumes Using NFS>>]

You can use either of the following methods to mount Gluster volumes:

* Gluster 3.2: Manually Mounting Volumes Using NFS[ Manually Mounting
Volumes Using NFS]
* Gluster 3.2: Automatically Mounting Volumes Using NFS[ Automatically
Mounting Volumes Using NFS]

Prerequisite: Install nfs-common package on both servers and clients
(only for Debian distribution), using the following command:

$ sudo aptitude install nfs-common

After mounting a volume, you can test the mounted volume using the
procedure described in Gluster 3.2: Testing Volumes Mounted Using NFS[
Testing Volumes Mounted Using NFS].

